
# IAM Detection Queries

## Process

- Ingested CloudTrail logs into Splunk
- Parsed JSON records using `spath` and `mvexpand`
- Built detection queries focused on IAM activity and identity behavior

---

## IAM User Creation

spl
index=* sourcetype=_json
| spath path=Records{} output=record
| mvexpand record
| spath input=record
| search eventName="CreateUser"
| table eventTime userIdentity.arn sourceIPAddress requestParameters.userName

DeleteUser
index=* sourcetype=_json
| spath path=Records{} output=record
| mvexpand record
| spath input=record
| search eventName="DeleteUser"
| table eventTime userIdentity.arn requestParameters.userName sourceIPAddress

Role Assumption
index=* sourcetype=_json
| spath path=Records{} output=record
| mvexpand record
| spath input=record
| search eventName="AssumeRole"
| table eventTime eventSource userIdentity.arn sourceIPAddress requestParameters.roleArn

Failed Privilege
index=* sourcetype=_json
| spath path=Records{} output=record
| mvexpand record
| spath input=record
| search errorCode=*
| table eventTime eventSource eventName errorCode userIdentity.arn sourceIPAddress

Identity Enumeration
index=* sourcetype=_json
| spath path=Records{} output=record
| mvexpand record
| spath input=record
| search eventName IN ("ListUsers","ListRoles","GetCallerIdentity")
| stats count by eventName userIdentity.arn
| sort -count
